The Health Access Innovation Act addresses the care access crisis by investing in trusted faith and community-based groups, covering medical costs, and supporting healthcare professionals who address social determinants of health. 

These local leaders are on the frontlines of fighting disparities, and this bill gives them the resources to expand care so families in the #FightingFifth and nationwide can live healthier lives, no matter their ZIP code or bank account.

This funding will support the purchase of four tractor-trailers and six box trucks to transport nutritious food to families in the #FightingFifth and across our state, directly delivering life-changing support.
